{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-share-image-js","path":"/3-invitations-to-try-atom-io/image_tw","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Luciano Mammino \"Loige\" - FullStack & Cloud developer, fighter, butterfly maker!","author":"Luciano Mammino","siteUrl":"https://loige.co","twitterProfile":"loige","disqusShortName":"loige"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0228aae0-cc39-52b0-a941-a2061e6cf82d","timeToRead":1,"headings":[],"html":"<p>I have finally got my invitation to try the new text editor <a href=\"https://atom.io\">Atom.io</a>. Atom is built with web technologies (node.js in it’s core) by the folks at GitHub and it’s somewhat very similar to the famous <a href=\"http://www.sublimetext.com/\">SublimeText</a>.\nIn my opinion it seems very promising (even if it’s significantly slower than SublimeText), anyway I have to try it a lot more before shaping a serious opinion about it.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1024px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.328125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/8d3d1/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.webp 256w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/354cf/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.webp 512w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/44907/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.webp 1024w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/5bb53/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.webp 1200w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/85b06/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.png 256w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/bc282/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.png 512w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/f1720/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.png 1024w,\n/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/5ece7/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.png 1200w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/5707dec0d091f2c9f03d0bc1ae9f07dd/f1720/Schermata-2014-04-09-alle-12-55-17.png\"\n            alt=\"Atom.io screenshoot\"\n            title=\"Atom.io screenshoot\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The point of this topic is that Atom.io is currently in closed beta and I have received 3 invitations to share with whom is willing to try it.</p>\n<p>I would be glad to <strong>share the invitations</strong> with the first 3 readers who would <strong>follow me</strong> on <a href=\"https://github.com/lmammino\">GitHub</a> or <a href=\"https://twitter.com/loige\">Twitter</a> <strong>and write a comment</strong> on this post.</p>\n<p>PS: You would probably need a GitHub account!</p>\n<p><strong>UPDATE</strong>, April 12:\nSorry guys, my invitations have gone for now.\nAnyway it seems that GitHub distributes other invitations sometime. So if you haven’t been in time you can still write a comment and if I ever manage to have other invites i will follow the order of the order to share them with you.</p>\n<p>Hope you will enjoy it.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"3 invitations to try Atom.io","slug":"3-invitations-to-try-atom-io","author":"Luciano Mammino","tags":["atom-io"],"date":"April 09, 2014","header_img":{"publicURL":"/static/4859ca3c8042da5689f0d401615827b2/3-invitations-to-try-atom-io.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"3-invitations-to-try-atom-io","width":440,"height":220,"type":"twitter"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}